  <body> <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode">🌙 Dark Mode</button>
    <p>R -ABOPT ONSET</p>
    <p> ATRIAL</p>
    <p> JUNCTIONAL</p>
    <p> VT</p>
    <ol>
      <li>A/R</li>
      <li>ASSOCIATE c SYNCOPE </li>
    </ol>
    <p>POLYURIA</p>
    <ol>
      <li>DRUGS - SYMPATHOMYMETICS</li>
    </ol>
    <p> DIGOXIN</p>
    <p> VASODIALATORS</p>
    <ol>
      <li>.</li>
    </ol>
    <h4>Palpitations</h4>
    <p></p>
    <div class="cardiac endocrine psych emergency General">
      <!-- S: Site / Sensation -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>:
            Sensation &amp; Rhythm (Tap it out)</span>
          <ul>
            <li><b>THE "CLINICAL DRUMMING":</b> Ask the patient to tap the
              rhythm on their chest or the table.
              <ul>
                <li><u>Fast &amp; Regular:</u> <span class="cardiac">SVT, VT,
                    Sinus Tachycardia.</span></li>
                <li><u>Fast &amp; Irregular:</u> <span class="cardiac">Atrial
                    Fibrillation (AF).</span></li>
                <li><u>"Skipped" or "Dropped" Beats:</u> <span class="cardiac">Ectopics
                    (PVCs/PACs) - "Flip-flop" sensation.</span></li>
                <li><u>Strong/Pounding (Normal Rate):</u> <span class="psych">Anxiety</span>,
                  <span class="cardiac">Valve disease (AR)</span>, <span class="endocrine">Thyrotoxicosis</span>.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Can you tap out on the table what your heart feels
          like when this happens? Does it feel like a fluttering, a racing, or a
          hard pounding?"</span> </div>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>:
            Onset &amp; Termination</span>
          <ul>
            <li><b>SUDDEN ON/OFF (Switch-like):</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="cardiac"><b>SVT</b> (Supraventricular Tachycardia).
                  Classic history.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b>GRADUAL ONSET / OFFSET:</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="General"><b>Sinus Tachycardia</b> (Response to
                  stress, exercise, fever, anemia).</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b>PRECIPITANTS:</b>
              <ul>
                <li>Exercise, Caffeine, Alcohol, Stress.</li>
                <li>Post-prandial (after eating) -&gt; Vagal tone issues.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Does the racing start instantly like someone
          flipped a light switch, or does it speed up gradually? How does it
          stop?"</span> </div>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>:
            Duration &amp; Frequency</span>
          <ul>
            <li>Seconds (Ectopics).</li>
            <li>Minutes to Hours (SVT, A-Fib).</li>
            <li>Continuous (Thyrotoxicosis, Anemia, Anxiety).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How long do these episodes last? How often do you
          get them?"</span> </div>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
            Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span>
          <ul>
            <li><b>AGGRAVATING:</b>
              <ul>
                <li><b>Stimulants:</b> Coffee, Energy drinks, Cocaine,
                  Amphetamines.</li>
                <li><b>Alcohol:</b> "Holiday Heart Syndrome" (Acute A-Fib after
                  binge).</li>
                <li><b>Position:</b> Lying on left side (makes ectopics more
                  noticeable).</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b>RELIEVING (Vagal Maneuvers):</b>
              <ul>
                <li>Deep breathing, holding breath (Valsalva), splashing cold
                  water on face.</li>
                <li><b>SVT</b> often terminates with these maneuvers.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Do you notice it more after coffee or alcohol? Is
          there anything you can do, like holding your breath, that stops it?"</span>
      </div>
      <!-- C: Character -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
            Character (Forcefulness)</span>
          <ul>
            <li><b>"FLUTTERING"</b> in chest or throat: <span class="cardiac">Atrial
                Fibrillation / Flutter.</span></li>
            <li><b>"POUNDING"</b> (can hear heartbeat in ears): <span class="cardiac">Aortic
                Regurgitation</span>, <span class="endocrine">Hyperthyroidism</span>,
              <span class="psych">Severe Anxiety</span>.</li>
            <li><b>"SKIPPED BEAT":</b> <span class="cardiac">Premature
                Ventricular/Atrial Contractions (PVCs/PACs).</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Does it feel like a butterfly fluttering, or like
          a hammer pounding against your ribs?"</span> </div>
      <!-- R: Radiation (Systemic Causes) -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
            R</span>
          <ul>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Have you lost weight recently? Do you feel shaky
          or prefer cold weather?"</span> </div>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms (The Red Flags) -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
            Associated Symptoms (Hemodynamic Stability)</span>
          <ul>
            <li><b>SYNCOPE / PRE-SYNCOPE (Passing out):</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="cardiac emergency"><b>MAJOR RED FLAG.</b> Suggests
                  the arrhythmia is causing low blood pressure (VT, Heart Block,
                  AS).</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b>CHEST PAIN:</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="cardiac emergency">Suggests Ischemia (supply/demand
                  mismatch) or that the pain is causing the tachycardia.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b>SHORTNESS OF BREATH:</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="cardiac">Suggests Heart Failure or PE.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b>THYROID:</b> Weight loss, heat intolerance, tremor.</li>
            <li><b>ANEMIA:</b> Fatigue, pallor, heavy periods (Menorrhagia).</li>
            <li><b>PHEOCHROMOCYTOMA:</b> Rare adrenal tumor -&gt; Triad of
              Headache + Sweating + Palpitations.</li>
            <li><b>PANIC SYMPTOMS:</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="psych">Tingling hands/lips, feeling of doom,
                  hyperventilation.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"When your heart races, do you ever feel
          lightheaded like you might pass out? Do you get any chest pain?"</span>
      </div>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
            Progression</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Are the episodes becoming more frequent or lasting
          longer?"</span> </div>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
            Pattern</span>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Nocturnal:</b> Waking up with it? (Sleep Apnea / Paroxysmal
              AF).</li>
            <li><b>Exertional:</b> Occurs during exercise? (Structural heart
              disease / Ischemia).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Does this happen while you are exercising, or only
          when you are resting?"</span> </div>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>:
            Effect on Life</span>
          <ul>
            <li>Fear of exercise or leaving the house.</li>
            <li>Interference with sleep.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Are you avoiding exercise because you're afraid of
          bringing it on?"</span> </div>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
            Red Flags (Family &amp; History)</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="cardiac emergency"><b>FAMILY HISTORY OF SUDDEN DEATH:</b>
              Specifically &lt; 40 years old (HOCM, Long QT, Brugada).</li>
            <li class="cardiac emergency"><b>HISTORY OF SYNCOPE</b> during
              palpitations.</li>
            <li class="cardiac"><b>STRUCTURAL HEART DISEASE:</b> Previous heart
              attack, valve surgery, or cardiomyopathy.</li>
            <li class="cardiac emergency"><b>EXERTIONAL ONSET:</b> Palpitations
              <i>during</i> active sport are dangerous until proven otherwise.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Has anyone in your family died suddenly at a young
          age? Have you ever passed out from this?"</span> </div>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>:
            Scale</span>
          <ul>
            <li>Severity of symptoms during the episode (0-10).</li>
            <li>EHRA Score (for Atrial Fibrillation symptoms).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 0 to 10, how distressing are these
          episodes?"</span> </div>
    </div>
